Added several spellings

1. Integrated parsha finding algorithm into real data/actually reading local MP3 files data to identify whether it contains a recognized parsha or not 2. Refactored what is now getParsha() into its own function(with two versions: 1. an overloaded version which doesn't print its findings to the console and accepts a dummy parameter called dontPrintToConsole of type boolean, 2. and one which does print its findings to the console) 3. Introduced a mutable map for rejects(rejected shiur title -> rejection reason) 4. Added function called findMP3sAndAddThemToListOfMp3s which finds all MP3 files in current directory and adds them to a list of files which it is given as a parameter, and returns true if there were no files at all in the given directory
Fixed spacing and nothing else.
